<div id="review_2173735695" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2173735695" />
    <a title="David Staniforth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16602614-david-staniforth"><img alt="David Staniforth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358713909p2/16602614.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2173735695?book_show_action=true">Nov 11, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="David Staniforth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="David Staniforth" href="/user/show/16602614-david-staniforth">David Staniforth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099582144" href="/book/show/23347044-the-son">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2173735695" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16554267748527599984">After reading and thoroughly enjoying Nesbo‚Äôs Headhunters, I dived into this one: my second Nesbo book. I almost gave up on it at chapter ten. Too many characters introduced too quickly, and too much chopping and changing from one scenario to another. Something, however, made me give it a little more time and by chapter 13 I was hooked to the point where I struggled to put it down. The characters just grew on me, I guess, and I needed to see where it was going to end up.<br/><br/>You almost lost me, Mr Ne</span>
  <span id="freeText16554267748527599984" style="display:none">After reading and thoroughly enjoying Nesbo‚Äôs Headhunters, I dived into this one: my second Nesbo book. I almost gave up on it at chapter ten. Too many characters introduced too quickly, and too much chopping and changing from one scenario to another. Something, however, made me give it a little more time and by chapter 13 I was hooked to the point where I struggled to put it down. The characters just grew on me, I guess, and I needed to see where it was going to end up.<br /><br />You almost lost me, Mr Nesbo, but you pulled me back in good style. A quarter of a star deducted for coming close to denying me an enjoyable read: 4.75 rounded up to 5.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16554267748527599984" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


